&lt;h2 id="1-introduction-and-goals"&gt;1. Introduction and Goals&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="11-purpose"&gt;1.1 Purpose&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SW360 is an open source software component management application designed for large organizations to track, manage, and ensure compliance of open source software components. This document provides a comprehensive architecture overview following the Arc42 template.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>SW360 Frontend Architecture</title><link>https://eclipse.dev/sw360/docs/architecture/sw360-frontend-architecture/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://eclipse.dev/sw360/docs/architecture/sw360-frontend-architecture/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sw360-frontend-architecture-documentation"&gt;SW360 Frontend Architecture Documentation&lt;/h1&gt;
